related_questions.question: What is Tilsit cheese similar to?
related_questions.snippet: Similar to Havarti, Tilsit has a fuller and more intense flavor than Havarti. With a brownish-orange washed rind and made of partially skimmed milk, this exquisite cheese has a rich yellow color with a springy elastic semi-firm texture, making it ideal for slicing.

related_questions.question: What does Tilsit cheese taste like?
related_questions.snippet: Young Tilsit cheese taste boasts a mild, creamy character with a subtle nuttiness reminiscent of Havarti or a young Gouda. Its texture is smooth and supple, yielding easily to the knife.
related_questions.title: What Does German Tilsit Cheese Taste Like - Ambassador Foods

related_questions.question: What is Tilsiter cheese used for?
related_questions.snippet: It is a common table cheese, yet versatile. Tilsit can be eaten cubed in salads, melted in sauces, on potatoes, in flans, or on burgers. Using the reimported recipe, Tilsiter has been manufactured in Switzerland since 1893 and in Germany since 1920, where it is known as the protected brand Holsteiner Tilsiter.
